      "level": {
        "value": 8
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> Pilts's executioner — a tongueless, one-eyed gnome berserker who calls the Emperor 'Unca Pit' and loves the guillotine like a pet. <strong>He never attacks gnomes</strong> unless struck first (Pilts knows never to order it). Understanding his babbling takes @Check[type:society|dc:20] (or Sense Motive at the GM's whim).</p><p><strong>Morale:</strong> fights to the death. If Pilts dies he freezes a round in shock, then resumes. If Pilts <strong>surrenders</strong> in his presence, Jabbyr snaps and attacks the ex-emperor for treason — and may demand the PCs help him strap 'Unca Pit' into the Tall Knife.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
